highlight.name: fec3e911-42bd-e3ed-ccf7-8f28983b4129
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: productivity = the ability of people to produce useful results at work.

highlight.name: 931c9bce-eaa2-8f5f-361f-f9673657002f
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: There are arguments on both sides, however, which we will discuss here.

freetext.name: c34c80fe-849c-82ba-52e2-f437e57c460e
freetext.subject: 打字机文本
freetext.title: 南京小骄傲
freetext.defaultappearance: 0 G 0 g 0 Tc 0 Tw 100 Tz 16.3 TL 0 Ts 0 Tr /AdobeSongStd-Light 12 Tf

highlight.name: e9d2b8f3-6502-4413-9e8e-f5ec085d3172
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: to subsidise = to pay part of the cost of something, usually in order to help people.

highlight.name: 94e2ec06-d2b0-2eaf-d5d1-48bfd624fb3b
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: perks = rewards from an employer which are not financial (eg free lunches, a car etc)

highlight.name: a32974ee-a4d8-9e19-0a93-4a19f35f9192
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: incentive = any reward that makes people work harder

highlight.name: 1334c2af-76df-6338-23b9-733c4c1727fd
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: on the job training = training while working, not by leaving work to go to college etc

highlight.name: 5a3e7ffa-6b2d-e1dc-9ba7-5ec25f17961f
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: day release programmes = programmes of training or education when employees can spend entire days out of work

highlight.name: dc6398bb-29ca-6ac3-732c-5b88eabf29b5
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: career progression = the ability to advance your career

highlight.name: 3151ae05-d53d-763f-2f6b-b8fc4814bbba
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: job prospects = the possibility of promotion or higher level work in future

highlight.name: 9261c501-4f65-9699-d0a9-fea1cf743c9c
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: redundancy = a situation where a worker loses their job because of changes in the company (not because of personal mistakes) (verb = to make someone redundant)

highlight.name: db995912-fb43-352d-31cf-e45fbf171170
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: to downsize = to make an organisation smaller and employ fewer people

highlight.name: 2102331b-7ba3-7716-a232-dd16704f83a3
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: to outsource = to stop doing work inside the company and send it to other companies or other countries, usually to save money

highlight.name: 889f8178-85c8-87e8-e609-6ebc27dd69bc
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: to restructure = to change the organisation of a company, usually in order to make it more effective or to save money.

highlight.name: 8e8e14a8-6ec4-8734-9c49-d64130f4840d
highlight.title: Guest
highlight.subject: 高亮
highlight.contents: the workforce = the total number of people working in an organisation, company or country
